arch:property.oc:show_val: Gray clayey mortar layer, 5YR6/1 (gray), extending throughout the trench, between the stylobates and rows of columns, and into the apsidal interior of the exedra. May represent a surface but in fact it is more likely that it is and accumulation of materials that are the product of industrial activity, such as a lime kiln. The layer is thickest in the west and against architecture, and is thinnest in the eastespecially north of the oblique intercolumnar wall. It would seem then that, after a period of abandonment or debris accumulation, the gray material was deposited between the west row of the East Colonnade and the center intercolumnar wall, and south of the oblique intercolumnar wall into the exedra.
Opening levels: 879.59 m at n; 880.25 at s.
Closing levels: 879.18 m at n; 879.76 m at s.
